;s Covered</h2><p style=\"font-family:var(--font-body);color:var(--text-2);line-height:1.75;font-size:1.0625rem\">Hunter Douglas offers a Limited Lifetime Warranty on most product lines — one of the strongest warranties in the window treatment industry. The warranty covers defects in materials and workmanship for the life of the product when purchased from an authorized dealer and professionally installed. Key points for Chicago homeowners: the warranty covers mechanism failures, fabric defects, and hardware issues. It does not cover damage from improper use, installation by non-certified installers, or purchases through unauthorized channels. As an authorized dealer, Ben&#x27;s Blinds handles all warranty claims directly with Hunter Douglas — you don&#x27;t need to navigate manufacturer customer service yourself.</p></div><div style=\"margin-bottom:1.75rem\"><h2 style=\"font-family:var(--font-display);font-weight:700;font-size:1.375rem;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:0.75rem;margin-top:0.25rem\">Duette Cellular Shades: Chicago&#x27;s Energy Efficiency Champion</h2><p style=\"font-family:var(--font-body);color:var(--text-2);line-height:1.75;font-size:1.0625rem\">Hunter Douglas Duette Honeycomb Shades are particularly relevant for Chicago homeowners given the city&#x27;s extreme temperature range (-20°F to 100°F). Duette Architella® — Hunter Douglas&#x27;s premium dual-cell Duette — uses a cell-within-a-cell structure that traps two layers of air, achieving the highest insulation rating of any off-the-shelf window treatment. In Chicago&#x27;s climate with 6,000+ heating degree days annually, Duette Architella shades can meaningfully reduce heating costs in older building stock with single or older double-pane windows. Hunter Douglas provides documented energy efficiency ratings for all Duette configurations, including R-value data for building permit and energy audit documentation.</p></div><div style=\"margin-bottom:1.75rem\"><h2 style=\"font-family:var(--font-display);font-weight:700;font-size:1.375rem;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:0.75rem;margin-top:0.25rem\">The Authorized Dealer Difference in Practice</h2><p style=\"font-family:var(--font-body);color:var(--text-2);line-height:1.75;font-size:1.0625rem\">When you purchase Hunter Douglas products through Ben&#x27;s Blinds, you receive: professional in-home measurement by Hunter Douglas-trained specialists; installation by certified Hunter Douglas installers; access to the full Hunter Douglas product catalog including dealer-exclusive lines; manufacturer warranty coverage with direct dealer support for claims; and access to Hunter Douglas&#x27;s rebate and promotional programs available only through authorized dealers. Big-box stores carry a limited selection of Hunter Douglas products under different product names, with standard (not lifetime) warranties, and without the professional measurement and installation that makes the difference between a perfect fit and a frustrating one.</p></div><div style=\"margin-bottom:1.75rem\"><h2 style=\"font-family:var(--font-display);font-weight:700;font-size:1.375rem;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:0.75rem;margin-top:0.25rem\">Schedule a Free Hunter Douglas Consultation</h2><p style=\"font-family:var(--font-body);color:var(--text-2);line-height:1.75;font-size:1.0625rem\">We bring actual Hunter Douglas product samples — fabric swatches, operating mechanism demonstrations, and PowerView motorization demos — to your home. For Chicago homeowners considering Hunter Douglas products, the in-home consultation is the most efficient way to evaluate options: you see the actual fabrics in your actual light, with your actual window dimensions and mount constraints already assessed. Our consultations are free with no obligation. Call 312.361.0908 or request a consultation online.</p></div><div style=\"margin-top:3rem;padding:2rem;background:var(--surface-2);border-radius:var(--radius);border-left:4px solid var(--brand)\"><p style=\"font-family:var(-